And you want to replace, you want to say, okay, I'm just going to look ahead, d equals one, that's all I can afford.

04:02.993 --> 04:08.181
I go ahead and at the end, I'm going to ask my neural network what the value here is.

04:09.325 --> 04:16.595
and the neural network will tell you accurately that the value at each of these nodes is zero.

04:16.615 --> 04:27.189
So the average value, if you can see right here, the average value of each of these nodes is zero, depending of course on how player two acts, but in this case it's zero.

04:27.830 --> 04:30.473
So as player one,

04:30.638 --> 04:37.330
this information will not lead you to the correct optimal conclusion, the correct optimal conclusion being this 0.4, 0.4, 0.2.

